properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 11 at 12:23PM PST until January 12 at 3:00PM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
...Large long-period northwest swells arriving this weekend...

A large swell train from the Gulf of Alaska has arrived today.
Northwest swells of 13 to 15 ft with a period of 16 to 18 seconds
will occur through the day causing breakers as high as 20 to 24
ft. Swells will start to decrease Sunday morning.

* WHAT...Large breaking waves of 20 to 24 feet.

* WHERE...Coastal North Bay Including Point Reyes National
Seashore, Southern Monterey Bay and Big Sur Coast, San
Francisco Peninsula Coast, San Francisco and Northern Monterey
Bay Counties.

* WHEN...to 3 PM PST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Dangerous swimming and surfing conditions and
localized beach erosion.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced swimmers should remain out of the water due to
dangerous surf conditions.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM PST SUNDAY
